news: England started its Live Earth concert at Wembley Stadium with an international drum tattoo: rockers at their kits, Scotsmen in kilts, Brazilian and Japanese and African drums. Then the show went decidedly British, mixing bombast, yearning and self-pity. The latest Genesis reunion did it with fast fingers and prog-rock intricacy; its all-purpose complaint about the state of the world, “Land of Confusion,” was still germane.
